<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<android.support.v4.widget.DrawerLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    android:id="@+id/drawer_layout"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:fitsSystemWindows="true">
    <RelativeLayout
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:background="@android:color/white">
        <include
            android:id="@+id/toolbar"
            layout="@layout/toolbar" />

        <ScrollView
            android:layout_below="@+id/toolbar"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content">

        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="match_parent"
            android:padding="10dp"
            android:orientation="vertical"
            android:background="@android:color/white">

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView1"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:padding="10dp"
                android:textSize="14sp"
                android:text="How to Twyst?"
                android:textColor="#555" />


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView2"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:padding="10dp"
                android:textSize="14sp"
                android:text="1. What are Twyst Bucks and what do I use them for?

Twyst Bucks are the currency you need to use some of the offers on Twyst. You earn Twyst

Bucks by inviting friends to Twyst, checking-in to outlets on Twyst, submitting offers and so on.

You spend Twyst Bucks to use some offers, extend your coupons and grab your friendsâ€™ coupons.

More detail below."
                android:textColor="#555"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView3"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:padding="10dp"
                android:textSize="14sp"
                android:text="2. Why should I upload the bill? Can I upload from home?

Uploading a bill is a way of letting Twyst know that you visited / order from a Twyst outlet. You

can upload your bills whether you went out to eat or ordered in. When an uploaded bill is

approved, you get a check-in at that outlet, and some Twyst Bucks!

One bill can be uploaded only once for approval. When we receive the bill, it goes through a 2-

part approval process, by Twyst and the outlet. The bill may be rejected for a variety of reasons,

and we will notify you of the reason for rejection."
                android:textColor="#555"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView4"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:padding="10dp"
                android:textSize="14sp"
                android:text="3. Lorem ipsum"
                android:textColor="#555"/>
        </LinearLayout>
        </ScrollView>



    </RelativeLayout>
    <include
        android:id="@+id/drawer_list"
        layout="@layout/drawer_list" />
</android.support.v4.widget.DrawerLayout>